pin. Indeed, we show that the Gilbert damping due to the\nquasi-particle spin current is strongly suppressed at low-temperatures, which\ngoes along with a shift of the precession frequency due to the condensate. The\nresults obtained may be of interest for on-going experiments in the field of\nmolecular spintronics.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 22 Feb 2010 12:34:03 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 25 Feb 2010 17:06:08 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 13 Apr 2010 17:27:56 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Wed, 5 May 2010 11:21:57 GMT"}],"update_date":"2010-05-06"}
